title: 1994 Porsche 911 Turbo 3.6
description: This 1994 Porsche 911 is one of a reported 754 Turbo 3.6 examples produced for the model year. It is powered by a turbocharged 3.6-liter flat-six paired with a five-speed manual transaxle, and it is finished in black over black leather. The car is equipped with 18" Speedline wheels, a Nakamichi radio, central locking, air conditioning, heated front seats, and a fixed rear spoiler. The current owner purchased the car circa 2014 and has since added approximately 500 miles of the 72k miles shown. Recent service included a fuel-system overhaul. This 964 is now offered on dealer consignment with service records, a copy of the Porsche Certificate of Authenticity, a clean Carfax report, and a clean Florida title.
author: bringatrailer
excerpt: Bid for the chance to own a 1994 Porsche 911 Turbo 3.6 at auction with Bring a Trailer, the home of the best vintage and classic cars online. Lot #203,056.
text: This 1994 Porsche 911 is one of a reported 754 Turbo 3.6 examples produced for the model year. It is powered by a turbocharged 3.6-liter flat-six paired with a five-speed manual transaxle, and it is finished in black over black leather. The car is equipped with 18″ Speedline wheels, a Nakamichi radio, central locking, air conditioning, heated front seats, and a fixed rear spoiler. The current owner purchased the car circa 2014 and has since added approximately 500 miles of the 72k miles shown. Recent service included a fuel-system overhaul. This 964 is now offered on dealer consignment with service records, a copy of the Porsche Certificate of Authenticity, a clean Carfax report, and a clean Florida title. The 964 Turbo featured widened bodywork when compared to the contemporary 911 and was fitted with aerodynamic side mirrors and a fixed rear spoiler. The 3.6-powered variant was introduced in January 1993, and this example is finished in Black (L741). Close-up photographs of the exterior finish and trim are shown in the gallery below. The multi-piece 18″ Speedline wheels are mounted with Michelin Pilot Sport tires. The Turbo features uprated brakes compared to the standard 964, including larger calipers and cross-drilled rotors at each corner. The heated power-adjustable front seats are trimmed in black leather with white piping, and the cabin features air conditioning, a Nakamichi radio, and central locking, and an aluminum shifter knob. The four-spoke leather-wrapped steering wheel frames a central tachometer with a 6,400-rpm redline as well as a 180-mph speedometer and gauges for oil pressure, oil temperature, oil level, and fuel level. The six-digit odometer shows 72k miles, approximately 500 of which were added during current ownership. The turbocharged 3.6-liter flat-six was factory rated at 355 horsepower and 384 lb-ft of torque. Invoices related to recent service are shown in the gallery below, and the engine was reassembled and the fuel system was overhauled in June 2025. Power is sent to the rear wheels through a five-speed manual transaxle. Additional photographs of the underside are shown in the gallery below. html:
This 1994 Porsche 911 is one of a reported 754 Turbo 3.6 examples produced for the model year. It is powered by a turbocharged 3.6-liter flat-six paired with a five-speed manual transaxle, and it is finished in black over black leather. The car is equipped with 18″ Speedline wheels, a Nakamichi radio, central locking, air conditioning, heated front seats, and a fixed rear spoiler. The current owner purchased the car circa 2014 and has since added approximately 500 miles of the 72k miles shown. Recent service included a fuel-system overhaul. This 964 is now offered on dealer consignment with service records, a copy of the Porsche Certificate of Authenticity, a clean Carfax report, and a clean Florida title.

The 964 Turbo featured widened bodywork when compared to the contemporary 911 and was fitted with aerodynamic side mirrors and a fixed rear spoiler.

The 3.6-powered variant was introduced in January 1993, and this example is finished in Black (L741). Close-up photographs of the exterior finish and trim are shown in the gallery below.

The multi-piece 18″ Speedline wheels are mounted with Michelin Pilot Sport tires. The Turbo features uprated brakes compared to the standard 964, including larger calipers and cross-drilled rotors at each corner.

The heated power-adjustable front seats are trimmed in black leather with white piping, and the cabin features air conditioning, a Nakamichi radio, and central locking, and an aluminum shifter knob.

The four-spoke leather-wrapped steering wheel frames a central tachometer with a 6,400-rpm redline as well as a 180-mph speedometer and gauges for oil pressure, oil temperature, oil level, and fuel level. The six-digit odometer shows 72k miles, approximately 500 of which were added during current ownership.

The turbocharged 3.6-liter flat-six was factory rated at 355 horsepower and 384 lb-ft of torque. Invoices related to recent service are shown in the gallery below, and the engine was reassembled and the fuel system was overhauled in June 2025.

Power is sent to the rear wheels through a five-speed manual transaxle. Additional photographs of the underside are shown in the gallery below.

Decoding the option sticker reveals the following information:

  • L741 – Black paint
  • VN – Black partial leather upholstery
  • C02 – Version for USA
  • XF5 – Leather-covered instrument rings
  • 139 – Seat heating, left
  • 340 – Seat heating, right
  • 407 – 18″ polished three-piece wheels
  • 513 – Power lumbar support, right
  • 586 – Power lumbar support, left
  • 650 – Power sunroof
  • 692 – Alpine-Porsche CDC-1 CD changer
  • 935 – Supple leather rear seats
  • 980 – Supple leather front seats

The Carfax report shows no accidents or damage.
